#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.45"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.45:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.45:0.2"
msgid "5. Dhammikavagga"
msgstr "5. About Dhammika"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.45:0.3"
msgid "45. Iṇasutta"
msgstr "45. Debt"

# Alternative title: “The Buddha predicts the history of late capitalism.”
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: Dāliddiyaṃ → dāḷiddiyaṃ (bj) | daḷiddiyaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.45:1.1"
msgid "“Dāliddiyaṃ, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, isn’t poverty suffering in the world for a person who enjoys "
"sensual pleasures?”"

msgctxt "an6.45:1.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. (1)"
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.352"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: daliddo → daḷiddo (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: anāḷhiko → anāḷhiyo (bj) | anāḷiko (si, pts1) | anaddhiko (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an6.45:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Yampi, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko iṇaṃ ādiyati, iṇādānampi, "
"bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“When a poor, penniless person falls into debt, isn’t being in debt also "
"suffering in the world for a person who enjoys sensual pleasures?”"

msgctxt "an6.45:2.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. (2)"
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Yampi, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko iṇaṃ ādiyitvā vaḍḍhiṃ "
"paṭissuṇāti, vaḍḍhipi, bhikkhave, dukkhā lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“When a poor person who has fallen into debt agrees to pay interest, isn’t "
"the interest also suffering in the world for a person who enjoys sensual "
"pleasures?”"

msgctxt "an6.45:3.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. (3)"
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: kālābhataṃ → kālagataṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an6.45:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Yampi, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko vaḍḍhiṃ paṭissuṇitvā kālābhataṃ "
"vaḍḍhiṃ na deti, codentipi naṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“When a poor person who has fallen into debt and agreed to pay interest "
"fails to pay it when it falls due, they get a warning."

msgctxt "an6.45:4.2"
msgid "codanāpi, bhikkhave, dukkhā lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Isn’t being warned suffering in the world for a person who enjoys sensual "
"pleasures?”"

msgctxt "an6.45:4.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. (4)"
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Yampi, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko codiyamāno na deti, anucarantipi "
"naṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“When a poor person fails to pay after getting a warning, they’re prosecuted."

msgctxt "an6.45:5.2"
msgid "anucariyāpi, bhikkhave, dukkhā lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Isn’t being prosecuted suffering in the world for a person who enjoys "
"sensual pleasures?”"

msgctxt "an6.45:5.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. (5)"
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:6.1"
msgid ""
"“Yampi, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko anucariyamāno na deti, "
"bandhantipi naṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“When a poor person fails to pay after being prosecuted, they’re imprisoned."

msgctxt "an6.45:6.2"
msgid "bandhanampi, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Isn’t being imprisoned suffering in the world for a person who enjoys "
"sensual pleasures?”"

msgctxt "an6.45:6.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. (6)"
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:7.1"
msgid ""
"“Iti kho, bhikkhave, dāliddiyampi dukkhaṃ lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino, iṇādānampi "
"dukkhaṃ lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino, vaḍḍhipi dukkhā lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino, codanāpi "
"dukkhā lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino, anucariyāpi dukkhā lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino, "
"bandhanampi dukkhaṃ lokasmiṃ kāmabhogino;"
msgstr ""
"“So mendicants, poverty, debt, interest, warnings, prosecution, and "
"imprisonment are suffering in the world for those who enjoy sensual "
"pleasures."

msgctxt "an6.45:7.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yassa kassaci saddhā natthi kusalesu dhammesu, hirī "
"natthi kusalesu dhammesu, ottappaṃ natthi kusalesu dhammesu, vīriyaṃ natthi "
"kusalesu dhammesu, paññā natthi kusalesu dhammesu—"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, whoever has no faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and "
"wisdom when it comes to skillful qualities"

msgctxt "an6.45:7.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyassa vinaye daliddo assako anāḷhiko."
msgstr "is called poor and penniless in the training of the noble one."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:8.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko saddhāya asati kusalesu "
"dhammesu, hiriyā asati kusalesu dhammesu, ottappe asati kusalesu dhammesu, "
"vīriye asati kusalesu dhammesu, paññāya asati kusalesu dhammesu, kāyena "
"duccaritaṃ carati, vācāya duccaritaṃ carati, manasā duccaritaṃ carati."
msgstr ""
"Since they have no faith, conscience, prudence, energy, or wisdom when it "
"comes to skillful qualities, they do bad things by way of body, speech, and "
"mind."

msgctxt "an6.45:8.2"
msgid "Idamassa iṇādānasmiṃ vadāmi."
msgstr "This is how they’re in debt, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.353"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
#. VAR: paṇidahati → padahati (mr)
msgctxt "an6.45:9.1"
msgid "So tassa kāyaduccaritassa paṭicchādanahetu pāpikaṃ icchaṃ paṇidahati."
msgstr ""
"In order to conceal the bad things they do by way of body, speech, and mind "
"they harbour corrupt wishes."

# Note the progression in these four terms.
msgctxt "an6.45:9.2"
msgid ""
"‘Mā maṃ jaññū’ti icchati, ‘mā maṃ jaññū’ti saṅkappati, ‘mā maṃ jaññū’ti "
"vācaṃ bhāsati, ‘mā maṃ jaññū’ti kāyena parakkamati. So tassa "
"vacīduccaritassa paṭicchādanahetu … pe … so tassa manoduccaritassa "
"paṭicchādanahetu … pe … ‘mā maṃ jaññū’ti kāyena parakkamati."
msgstr ""
"They wish, plan, speak, and act with the thought: ‘May no-one find me out!’"

msgctxt "an6.45:9.3"
msgid "Idamassa vaḍḍhiyā vadāmi."
msgstr "This is how they pay interest, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:10.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ pesalā sabrahmacārī evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Good-hearted spiritual companions say this about them:"

msgctxt "an6.45:10.2"
msgid "‘ayañca so āyasmā evaṅkārī evaṃsamācāro’ti."
msgstr "‘This venerable acts like this, and behaves like that.’"

msgctxt "an6.45:10.3"
msgid "Idamassa codanāya vadāmi."
msgstr "This is how they’re warned, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:11.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ araññagataṃ vā rukkhamūlagataṃ vā suññāgāragataṃ vā "
"vippaṭisārasahagatā pāpakā akusalavitakkā samudācaranti."
msgstr ""
"When they go to a wilderness, the root of a tree, or an empty hut, they’re "
"beset by remorseful, unskillful thoughts."

msgctxt "an6.45:11.2"
msgid "Idamassa anucariyāya vadāmi."
msgstr "This is how they’re prosecuted, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:12.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, bhikkhave, daliddo assako anāḷhiko kāyena duccaritaṃ caritvā "
"vācāya duccaritaṃ caritvā manasā duccaritaṃ caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā nirayabandhane vā bajjhati tiracchānayonibandhane vā."
msgstr ""
"That poor, penniless person has done bad things by way of body, speech, and "
"mind. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re trapped in the prison "
"of hell or the animal realm."

#. VAR: evaṃkaṭukaṃ → evaṃdukkhaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an6.45:12.2"
msgid ""
"Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, aññaṃ ekabandhanampi samanupassāmi evaṃdāruṇaṃ evaṃkaṭukaṃ "
"evaṃantarāyakaraṃ anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya, yathayidaṃ, "
"bhikkhave, nirayabandhanaṃ vā tiracchānayonibandhanaṃ vāti."
msgstr ""
"I don’t see a single prison that’s as brutal, as vicious, and such an "
"obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary as the prison of hell or the "
"animal realm."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:13.1"
msgid "Dāliddiyaṃ dukkhaṃ loke,"
msgstr "Poverty is said to be suffering in the world,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:13.2"
msgid "iṇādānañca vuccati;"
msgstr "and so is being in debt."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:13.3"
msgid "Daliddo iṇamādāya,"
msgstr "A poor person who has fallen in debt"

# I interpret this line a little differently to BB.
#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:13.4"
msgid "bhuñjamāno vihaññati."
msgstr "worries even when spending the loan."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:14.1"
msgid "Tato anucaranti naṃ,"
msgstr "And then they’re prosecuted,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:14.2"
msgid "bandhanampi nigacchati;"
msgstr "or even thrown in jail."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:14.3"
msgid "Etañhi bandhanaṃ dukkhaṃ,"
msgstr "Such imprisonment is true suffering"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:14.4"
msgid "kāmalābhābhijappinaṃ."
msgstr "for someone who prays for pleasure and possessions."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.354"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:15.1"
msgid "Tatheva ariyavinaye,"
msgstr "In the same way, in the noble one’s training"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:15.2"
msgid "saddhā yassa na vijjati;"
msgstr "whoever has no faith,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:15.3"
msgid "Ahirīko anottappī,"
msgstr "no conscience or prudence,"

# BB has no note, but the reading is obscure to me. PTS reads “vinicchaya”. Comm. “Pāpakammavinibbayoti pāpakammavaḍḍhako”, probably echoing the line a little further down. MA 125 has 作惡不善行 “do bad unskillful deeds”. Thanissaro translates “contemplating evil actions” which seems to fit the main text better.
#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:15.4"
msgid "pāpakammavinibbayo."
msgstr "contemplates bad deeds."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:16.1"
msgid "Kāyaduccaritaṃ katvā,"
msgstr "After doing bad things"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:16.2"
msgid "vacīduccaritāni ca;"
msgstr "by way of body,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:16.3"
msgid "Manoduccaritaṃ katvā,"
msgstr "speech, and mind,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:16.4"
msgid "‘mā maṃ jaññū’ti icchati."
msgstr "they wish, ‘May no-one find me out!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
#. VAR: saṃsappati → saṅkappati (mr)
msgctxt "an6.45:17.1"
msgid "So saṃsappati kāyena,"
msgstr "Their behavior is creepy"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:17.2"
msgid "vācāya uda cetasā;"
msgstr "by body, speech, and mind."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:17.3"
msgid "Pāpakammaṃ pavaḍḍhento,"
msgstr "They pile up bad deeds"

# This is an idiom. Compare Thag 2.32.
#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:17.4"
msgid "tattha tattha punappunaṃ."
msgstr "on and on, life after life."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:18.1"
msgid "So pāpakammo dummedho,"
msgstr "That stupid evildoer,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:18.2"
msgid "jānaṃ dukkaṭamattano;"
msgstr "knowing their own misdeeds,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:18.3"
msgid "Daliddo iṇamādāya,"
msgstr "is a poor person who has fallen in debt,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:18.4"
msgid "bhuñjamāno vihaññati."
msgstr "and worries even when spending the loan."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:19.1"
msgid "Tato anucaranti naṃ,"
msgstr "And when in village or wilderness"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:19.2"
msgid "saṅkappā mānasā dukhā;"
msgstr "they’re prosecuted"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:19.3"
msgid "Gāme vā yadi vāraññe,"
msgstr "by painful mental plans,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:19.4"
msgid "yassa vippaṭisārajā."
msgstr "which are born of remorse."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:20.1"
msgid "So pāpakammo dummedho,"
msgstr "That stupid evildoer,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:20.2"
msgid "jānaṃ dukkaṭamattano;"
msgstr "knowing their own misdeeds,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:20.3"
msgid "Yonimaññataraṃ gantvā,"
msgstr "goes to one of the animal realms,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:20.4"
msgid "niraye vāpi bajjhati."
msgstr "or is trapped in hell."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:21.1"
msgid "Etañhi bandhanaṃ dukkhaṃ,"
msgstr "Such imprisonment is true suffering,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:21.2"
msgid "yamhā dhīro pamuccati;"
msgstr "from which a wise one is released."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:21.3"
msgid "Dhammaladdhehi bhogehi,"
msgstr "With confident heart, they give"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:21.4"
msgid "dadaṃ cittaṃ pasādayaṃ."
msgstr "with wealth that is properly earned."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:22.1"
msgid "Ubhayattha kaṭaggāho,"
msgstr "That faithful householder"

# gharamesin = Skt gṛhamedhin = householder
#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:22.2"
msgid "saddhassa gharamesino;"
msgstr "wins both ways:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:22.3"
msgid "Diṭṭhadhammahitatthāya,"
msgstr "welfare and benefit in this life,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:22.4"
msgid "samparāyasukhāya ca;"
msgstr "and happiness in the next."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:22.5"
msgid "Evametaṃ gahaṭṭhānaṃ,"
msgstr "This is how, for a householder,"

# See BB’s note.
#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:22.6"
msgid "cāgo puññaṃ pavaḍḍhati."
msgstr "merit grows by generosity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:23.1"
msgid "Tatheva ariyavinaye,"
msgstr "In the same way, in the noble one’s training,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:23.2"
msgid "saddhā yassa patiṭṭhitā;"
msgstr "whoever is grounded in faith,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:23.3"
msgid "Hirīmano ca ottappī,"
msgstr "with conscience and prudence,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:23.4"
msgid "paññavā sīlasaṃvuto."
msgstr "wise, and restrained in ethical conduct,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:24.1"
msgid "Eso kho ariyavinaye,"
msgstr "is said to live happily"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:24.2"
msgid "‘sukhajīvī’ti vuccati;"
msgstr "in the noble one’s training."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:24.3"
msgid "Nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ laddhā,"
msgstr "After gaining spiritual bliss,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:24.4"
msgid "upekkhaṃ adhitiṭṭhati."
msgstr "they concentrate on equanimity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:25.1"
msgid "Pañca nīvaraṇe hitvā,"
msgstr "They give up the five hindrances,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:25.2"
msgid "niccaṃ āraddhavīriyo;"
msgstr "constantly energetic,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:25.3"
msgid "Jhānāni upasampajja,"
msgstr "and enter the absorptions,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:25.4"
msgid "ekodi nipako sato."
msgstr "unified, self-disciplined, and mindful."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:26.1"
msgid "Evaṃ ñatvā yathābhūtaṃ,"
msgstr "Truly knowing in this way"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:26.2"
msgid "sabbasaṃyojanakkhaye;"
msgstr "the end of all fetters,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:26.3"
msgid "Sabbaso anupādāya,"
msgstr "by not grasping in any way,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:26.4"
msgid "sammā cittaṃ vimuccati."
msgstr "their mind is rightly freed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:27.1"
msgid "Tassa sammā vimuttassa,"
msgstr "To that poised one, rightly freed"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:27.2"
msgid "ñāṇañce hoti tādino;"
msgstr "with the end of the fetters of rebirth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:27.3"
msgid "‘Akuppā me vimuttī’ti,"
msgstr "the knowledge comes:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:27.4"
msgid "bhavasaṃyojanakkhaye."
msgstr "‘My freedom is unshakable.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "an6.45:28.1"
msgid "Etaṃ kho paramaṃ ñāṇaṃ,"
msgstr "This is the ultimate knowledge."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:28.2"
msgid "etaṃ sukhamanuttaraṃ;"
msgstr "This is the supreme happiness."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:28.3"
msgid "Asokaṃ virajaṃ khemaṃ,"
msgstr "Sorrowless, stainless, secure:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.45:28.4"
msgid "etaṃ ānaṇyamuttaman”ti."
msgstr "this is the highest freedom from debt.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.45:28.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
